  "articleSummary": "**Summary**\n\n\"Into the Breach\" is a technical analysis and defensive guide addressing the evolving landscape of supply chain attacks and developer-targeted exploits. The article argues that modern developer environments have become \"credential warehouses\" where local convenience creates catastrophic security risks, rendering traditional \"be careful\" advice obsolete. Using a proactive and pragmatic tone, the author advocates for a \"defense-in-depth\" strategy centered on filesystem isolation (DevContainers), strict secret scoping, and the aggressive deployment of \"canary tokens\" as digital tripwires. The intended audience is software engineers and DevOps professionals who must shift from a model of human vigilance to one of structural containment to mitigate risks like infostealers and prompt injection.",
